# =============================================================================
# .gitignore — loss-function-driven-agentic-loops
# =============================================================================
# Every file in this repo is either:
#   (a) source — tracked
#   (b) build artifact from a tool the user might invoke — ignored
#   (c) runtime state from the loss-function-driven loop — ignored
#   (d) per-machine scratch — ignored
#
# When adding to this file, group by what tool produced the artifact,
# not by the artifact itself. New contributors should be able to find
# the section that matches their tool.
# =============================================================================

# ----- OS / editor -----
.DS_Store
.DS_Store?
._*
.Spotlight-V100
.Trashes
ehthumbs.db
Thumbs.db
desktop.ini
*~
*.swp
*.swo
*.swn
.vscode/
.idea/
*.iml
*.code-workspace

# ----- Shell tooling -----
# Backup / editor / tempfile suffixes that editors add
\#*\#
.\#*
*.bak
*.orig
*.rej

# =============================================================================
# Bundle-side artifacts (these come from running install.sh, the
# installer, or the loop driver in real projects the bundle is
# applied to — NOT from working on the bundle itself)
# =============================================================================

# Per-cycle loop artifacts (generated by cycle.sh, regenerated
# every run, never committed)
.iterations/
logs/cycle-*/
logs/best-cycle.json
logs/iteration-log.md
logs/.loop_start_ts
logs/tokens_used.txt
logs/tokens_last_cycle.txt
logs/design-set-score.json
logs/held-out-score.json

# Per-task scratch inside the verifier project
logs/<task>.log          # but VERIFIER-LEVEL logs/iteration-log.md
                         # and logs/best-cycle.json ARE committed
                         # by intent — they're the "what was tested"
                         # artifact. See examples/lfd-system-verifier/README.md.

# Agent-specific config (these only exist inside a real project
# that uses the bundle, not in the bundle repo itself)
.claude/
.codex/
.opencode/
.hermes-worktrees/
.fake-skills/

# Loop-driver symlink (created at runtime by run-verification.sh,
# not part of the committed tree)
examples/lfd-system-verifier/loop-driver

# =============================================================================
# Language toolchains (contributors may run one of these locally)
# =============================================================================

# Python
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
*$py.class
*.egg-info/
.eggs/
build/
dist/
.pytest_cache/
.mypy_cache/
.ruff_cache/
.coverage
.coverage.*
htmlcov/
.tox/
.nox/

# Virtualenvs
.venv/
venv/
env/
ENV/

# Node / TypeScript (the bundle's adapter docs reference
# @anthropic-ai/claude-code, @openai/codex, opencode-ai — contributors
# may install one to test the adapter contract)
node_modules/
.npm
.yarn
.pnp.*
*.tsbuildinfo
.next/
.nuxt/
.turbo/
.vercel/

# Rust (example /goal prompts may scaffold Rust projects)
target/
**/*.rs.bk
Cargo.lock

# Go
vendor/
*.test
*.out

# =============================================================================
# Per-machine scratch (should never be in any user's repo)
# =============================================================================

# Process / session DBs (Hermes, etc.) — only relevant if someone
# runs the verifier from inside a Hermes session and accidentally
# CWDs into the repo. Defensive.
*.db
*.db-shm
*.db-wal

# Local-only tool configs that some agents drop
.env
.env.local
.env.*.local

# Editor swap / autosave (covered by *~ but explicit doesn't hurt)
*.tmp
*.swp
*.swo
logs/*.tsv
